================================================================================
SCOPE NOTICE — what this MIT license does and does not cover
================================================================================

This MIT license covers ONLY the original wrapper/glue code in this repository
(the ComfyUI nodes, the subprocess worker orchestration, the offloading device
shuffling, and the setup scripts).

IT DOES NOT COVER:

1. MV-SAM3D (https://github.com/devinli123/MV-SAM3D). This repository does NOT
   redistribute any MV-SAM3D code. It references the upstream repository as a
   git submodule (vendor/MV-SAM3D) — a pointer that is fetched from upstream
   onto YOUR machine when you initialize it. MV-SAM3D is distributed by its
   authors under Meta's SAM License (a non-permissive license with its own
   terms and restrictions). By initializing the submodule and running this
   wrapper, you accept those terms directly from upstream. Review them before
   any use, especially commercial use.

2. Meta SAM 3D Objects (model weights and engine). Not contained, fetched, or
   redistributed here. Governed by Meta's SAM License. The weights are
   downloaded by the separate ComfyUI-SAM3DObjects pack; its obligations flow
   through to you.

3. ComfyUI-SAM3DObjects (https://github.com/PozzettiAndrea/ComfyUI-SAM3DObjects,
   GPL-3.0). This wrapper does not import, link, or redistribute its code. It
   only executes the standalone Python interpreter of the pixi environment that
   pack provisions, as a subprocess. The GPL-3.0 governs that pack, not this
   one.

ATTRIBUTION: If you use this wrapper in academic or published work, cite the
MV-SAM3D paper (arXiv:2603.11633) and Meta SAM 3D Objects. All credit for the
multi-view fusion method belongs to the MV-SAM3D authors; all credit for the
underlying 3D reconstruction belongs to Meta AI Research.

TRADEMARKS: "SAM", "SAM 3D", "Segment Anything", and "Meta" are trademarks of
Meta Platforms, Inc. This project is not affiliated with, endorsed by, or
sponsored by Meta or the MV-SAM3D authors — hence "Unofficial".
